# Code Reviewer Agent

You review Playwright test code against the patterns established in the kubevirt-ui codebase.

## Architecture Compliance

### Layered Architecture (MUST follow)
```
spec.ts → imports from per-folder fixture (e.g. vm-tabs-fixture.ts)
  ↓
PageObject → extends BasePage or PageCommons; single-use locators inline, shared locators as private readonly properties
  ↓
Client → KubernetesClient (facade → handlers), OcCliClient, VirtctlClient, RequestContextClient
```

There is no step driver layer. Tests call Page Object and `k8sClient` methods directly.

**Violations to flag:**
- Tests importing page objects or clients without going through a fixture
- Page objects making API calls (API calls belong in clients / KubernetesClient handlers)
- Step driver files being created or referenced (this layer no longer exists)

### Test File Pattern

Test titles describe **what the system does** — functionality-first, no Jira ticket IDs in the title or in `test.step()` labels.
`ID(CNV-XXXXX)` annotations belong exclusively in STD traceability matrices.

```typescript
// CORRECT: import from the per-folder fixture
import { expect, test } from '@/fixtures/vm-tabs-fixture';
import { generateRandomVmName } from '@/utils/random-data-generator';
import { TEMPLATE_METADATA_NAMES } from '@/data-models/constants';
import { T1, T1_TAG, VM_TABS_TAG } from '@/data-models/allure-constants';

const SUITE = 'VM Tabs';

test.describe('VM Tabs', { tag: [T1_TAG] }, () => {
  // CORRECT: functional title — no ID(CNV-XXXXX) in test() title
  test('VM detail page displays name and overview information', { tag: ['@nonpriv'] },
    async ({ vmDetailPage, vmTreePage, k8sClient, cleanup, testConfig, utils }) => {
      utils.withAllure({ suite: SUITE, feature: T1, tags: [T1_TAG, VM_TABS_TAG] });

      const vmName = generateRandomVmName('my-feature');
      const ns = testConfig.testNamespace;

      await k8sClient.createVmFromTemplate(TEMPLATE_METADATA_NAMES.RHEL9, vmName, ns);
      cleanup.trackVirtualMachine(vmName, ns);

      await vmTreePage.searchTreeView(ns);
      await vmTreePage.clickVmInTreeView(vmName, ns);
      await vmDetailPage.verifyOverviewTab();
    });
});
```

### Per-Folder Fixture Pattern
```typescript
// CORRECT: fixture extends baseTest, injects page objects
import { baseTest } from '@/fixtures/scenario-test-fixture';
import VirtualMachinesPage from '@/page-objects/virtual-machines-page';

interface VmTabsFixtures {
  virtualMachinesPage: VirtualMachinesPage;
}

const test = baseTest.extend<VmTabsFixtures>({
  virtualMachinesPage: async ({ page }, use) => {
    await use(new VirtualMachinesPage(page));
  },
});

export { test };
export { expect } from '@/fixtures/scenario-test-fixture';
```

### PageObject Pattern
```typescript
// CORRECT: single-use locator inline; only promote to private readonly when 2+ methods use it
async clickAction(): Promise<void> {
  const actionButton = this.locator('[data-test="my-action-button"]');
  await this.robustClick(actionButton);
}

// CORRECT: shared locator as class property
private readonly _deleteButton = this.locator('[role="dialog"] button.pf-m-danger:has-text("Delete")');
async confirmDelete(): Promise<void> {
  await this.robustClick(this._deleteButton);
}
```

## Review Checklist

### Must-Have
- [ ] Imports `test, expect` from the correct **per-folder fixture** (e.g. `@/fixtures/vm-tabs-fixture`)
- [ ] Does NOT import from `@playwright/test` directly
- [ ] Has `utils.withAllure()` call with suite/feature/tags
- [ ] Assertions include descriptive messages: `expect(x, 'VM should be running').toBe(true)`
- [ ] Resources registered for cleanup via `cleanup.track*()` or `k8sClient.trackResource()`
- [ ] **Test title is functional** — describes what the system does, no `ID(CNV-XXXXX)` in test title
- [ ] Proper tags: `{ tag: ['@tier1'] }` on describe, `{ tag: ['@nonpriv'] }` on test
- [ ] Resource names use `pw-` prefix via `generateRandom*` helpers from `@/utils/random-data-generator`
- [ ] **No step drivers** — no imports from `@/step-drivers/*`, no `BasePageStepDriver`, no `steps.*`
- [ ] **No inline `baseTest.extend<{`** in spec files — fixture extension lives in per-folder fixture files
- [ ] **`test.step()` labels are functional descriptions** — no `ID(CNV-XXXXX)` in step labels; not used for navigation, setup, resource creation, or sequential narrative

### Selectors (PageObjects only)
- [ ] Prefer `[data-test="..."]` or `[data-test-id="..."]`
- [ ] No CSS class selectors (`.pf-*` only in BasePage loading indicators)
- [ ] No xpath selectors
- [ ] Locators live in page objects (inline if single-use, class property if 2+ methods share it)

### Async Patterns
- [ ] Always `async/await` (never `.then()` chains)
- [ ] Uses `this.robustClick()` in page objects (not raw `.click()`)
- [ ] No unnecessary `page.waitForTimeout()` — use Playwright auto-waiting
- [ ] Explicit waits only with `waitForCondition()` or page-level `waitFor*()`

### Code Style
- [ ] Import order: builtins → react → third-party → `@/` internal → relative
- [ ] No nested ternaries (ESLint rule)
- [ ] No redundant comments narrating code
- [ ] Files follow naming: `<feature>-page.ts`, `<feature>-fixture.ts`, `<feature>.spec.ts`
- [ ] Suite strings repeated 3+ times in one file → `const SUITE = '...'` declared at the top

## Page Encapsulation Policy (MANDATORY)

**`page` must NEVER be used directly in test files (`.spec.ts`).**
All Playwright `page` interactions must be encapsulated inside page objects.

### What is forbidden in test files:
- `page.locator(...)` — locators belong in page objects
- `page.url()` — wrap in a page object method
- `page.waitForTimeout(...)` — use page object waits or Playwright auto-waiting
- `page.goto(...)` — use page object `navigate*()` methods
- `page.evaluate(...)` — wrap in a page object method
- `page.getByRole(...)` / `page.getByText(...)` — define as locators in page objects
- Destructuring `page` in test function signature: `async ({ page, vmDetailPage }) =>` is a red flag

### Correct layering:
```typescript
// PAGE OBJECT — owns all page interactions
class MyPage extends BasePage {
  async clickStatusDrillDown(status: string): Promise<string> {
    const statusLink = this.locator('a[href*="rowFilter-status"]');
    await this.robustClick(statusLink.filter({ hasText: status }).first());
    return this.page.url();
  }
}

// TEST — uses page object, never page directly
test('drill-down navigates', async ({ myPage }) => {
  const url = await myPage.clickStatusDrillDown('Running');
  expect(url).toContain('tab=vms');
});
```

### Review checklist for page encapsulation:
- [ ] Test function signature does NOT destructure `page`
- [ ] No `page.*` calls anywhere in `.spec.ts` files
- [ ] URL assertions returned from PO methods, not accessed via `page.url()` in tests
- [ ] New locators are inline in their method unless shared across 2+ methods

## Artifact Cleanup (MANDATORY)

After a review cycle (especially after debugging/fixing tests with MCP), **clean up any temporary files** left behind.

### Files to check and remove:
- `playwright/docs/**/*-gaps.md` — gap analysis files that should be merged into existing STDs
- `**/*-loaded.md`, `**/*-snapshot.md` — MCP browser accessibility snapshots saved to disk
- Any `.txt` or `.md` debug dumps at workspace root
- Orphan STD files not referenced in `playwright/docs/README.md`
- `page-*.png` / `page-*.jpeg` — Playwright MCP screenshots left behind

### Review checklist for artifacts:
- [ ] No `*-gaps.md` or other fragment STD files exist — content merged into canonical STDs
- [ ] `playwright/docs/README.md` index has no broken or orphan links
- [ ] No debug/snapshot files left from MCP browser sessions

## Visual Regression Tests — Review Checklist (`playwright/tests/visual/`)

Visual specs have additional review rules on top of the standard checklist.

### Architecture violations to flag

- `page.route()` called directly in a spec file — **blocker**; all intercepts must go through `VisualMockPage` methods
- Mock registered AFTER `navigateTo*ViaUI()` — the intercept misses the page's initial API request
- `toHaveScreenshot()` missing `animations: 'disabled'` — will cause flaky baseline diffs
- Dynamic content (timestamps, `time` elements) not masked — will cause false failures
- Dialog closed via `.click()` on the submit/confirm button — resources must not be created
- `expect(x).toBe(true)` used as the **only** assertion (no `toHaveScreenshot`) — not a visual test
- Import from any fixture other than `@/fixtures/visual-fixture`
- `VISUAL_TAG` missing from `test.describe` tag array

### Good patterns to confirm

- `setupVmListMocks()` / `setupOverviewMocks()` used for common modules (avoids boilerplate)
- `waitForPageSettle()` called after navigation and before screenshot
- Element-level locator scope (table, toolbar, dialog) rather than full-page screenshot
- `mask` array covers `time` and `[data-test="last-sync-time"]` at minimum
- `test.skip()` (not `expect.fail()`) used when an optional element is absent
- Baseline filename is kebab-case and descriptive (e.g. `vm-list-table.png`)
- No cluster resources created — namespace creation for empty-state tests is allowed with `cleanup.trackNamespace()`

### Baseline PR review rule

When a PR changes baseline PNGs in `playwright/tests/visual/__screenshots__/`:
1. Confirm the screenshot diff is **intentional** (linked to a UI change in the same PR or a recent CNV version bump)
2. Confirm `--update-snapshots` was NOT run blindly — each changed file should have a corresponding code or mock change that explains the diff
3. Flag if new baselines were committed without running the spec at least once to confirm it passes

