## Linting & Formatting (MANDATORY)

After reviewing code, **always run `npm run lint:fix`** on all modified files and fix any remaining issues.

1. Run `npm run lint:fix`
2. Run `npx tsc --project playwright/tsconfig.json --noEmit` to catch type errors
3. Any new type errors introduced by the changes must be fixed

## MCP Review Aids (`kubevirt-ui-mcp`)

Use `kubevirt-ui-mcp` tools for all review analysis:

**Coverage tools:**
- `get_orphan_page_object_methods` — flag page object methods that lost their last caller
- `get_coverage_for_feature` — check if the feature area under review has adequate coverage
- `find_tests_by_jira` — verify the Jira ticket referenced in `ID(CNV-XXXXX)` has matching test coverage

After reviewing changes that added or removed methods, call `invalidate_cache`.

**Linter tools (spec convention enforcement — use on every PR review):**

| Review task | Tool |
|---|---|
| Check spec file for convention violations | `lint_spec_file path=<spec>` |
| Verify Jira IDs from specs are documented in STD | `validate_std_coverage` |
| Confirm API/UI test parity after new UI write tests | `check_api_ui_parity` |
| Get authoritative allure tag constants (verify PR uses correct ones) | `get_allure_suite_map` |

**`lint_spec_file` checks**:
- Raw `page` usage instead of page objects
- Hardcoded timeouts instead of `TestTimeouts` constants
- Missing `cleanup.track*()` calls after resource creation
- Direct API calls without going through fixture clients

> Note: `lint_spec_file` may flag missing `ID(CNV-XXXXX)` annotations in test titles. This check is superseded by the functionality-first naming convention — test titles must be functional descriptions; Jira IDs belong in STD traceability matrices.

Run `lint_spec_file` on every new or modified `.spec.ts` file before approving a PR. Raw `page` usage, hardcoded timeouts, and missing cleanup tracking are blockers.

## Common Anti-Patterns

```typescript
// BAD: Ticket-first test title
test('ID(CNV-78882) Cluster overview widgets: status, health, allocation', ...)
// GOOD: Functionality-first test title
test('Cluster overview displays status, health, and resource allocation widgets', ...)

// BAD: Direct page access in test
test('example', async ({ page, virtualMachinesPage }) => {
  await page.locator('[data-test="vm-list"]').click();
});
// GOOD: Via page object
test('example', async ({ virtualMachinesPage }) => {
  await virtualMachinesPage.clickVmList();
});

// BAD: Inline baseTest.extend in spec file
const test = baseTest.extend<{ myPage: MyPage }>({
  myPage: async ({ page }, use) => { await use(new MyPage(page)); },
});
// GOOD: Fixture extension lives in a per-folder fixture file

// BAD: Importing from a step driver (the layer no longer exists)
import KubernetesStepDriver from '@/step-drivers/kubernetes-step-driver';
// GOOD: Use k8sClient from the fixture directly

// BAD: hardcoded wait
await page.waitForTimeout(5000);
// GOOD: Condition-based wait
await this.pageObject.verifyPageLoaded();

// BAD: Missing data-test selectors
await this.locator('.pf-v5-c-button--primary').click();
// GOOD: Data-test attribute
await this.locator('[data-test="create-vm-button"]').click();

// BAD: Positional selector
await this.locator('td').nth(3).click();
// GOOD: Semantic or data-test selector
await this.locator('[data-label="Status"]').click();

// BAD: test.step() as a sequential narrative / comment substitute
await test.step('Navigate to VM list and open wizard', async () => {
  await virtualMachinesPage.navigateToVirtualMachinesViaUI();
  await createVmPage.openCreateVmWizard();
});
await test.step('Step 1 — Verify Deployment Details', async () => {
  await createVmPage.verifyDeploymentDetailsStep();
});
// GOOD: implementation inline, no wrapper
await virtualMachinesPage.navigateToVirtualMachinesViaUI();
await createVmPage.openCreateVmWizard();
await createVmPage.verifyDeploymentDetailsStep();

// GOOD: test.step() with functional label grouping logical assertions
await test.step('Migration section heading reads "Migration statuses"', async () => {
  const title = await virtualMachinesPage.getMigrationStatusSectionTitle();
  expect(title).toBe('Migration statuses');
});
```
